  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (dd7c88f 2022-07-08T00:23:23.289481Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (Intel)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nIf you type `forge` to get the help menu, you'll see\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n[...]\r\nscript              Run a smart contract as a script, building transactions that can be sent onchain. [aliases: s]\r\nsnapshot            Create a snapshot of each test's gas usage. [aliases: s]\r\n[...]\r\n```\r\n\r\nRunning `forge s` it will try to run `forge script` as far as I see.",
